Yes. And then after that - I - I got into the Civil Service through a found about way. Well, the - I'd been paid paid off from this other job, and - and the - the Ministry o
f Labour were then being - being formed and they - they wanted temporary clerks and I got a job as a temporary clerk in - in the Ministry of Labour which was of course a branch of the Civil Service. And I started there, I can remember my - the - the wage 
there because I was getting sixpence an hour, and we had to work fifty hours a week. So I got twenty-five bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3539663 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12722762\charrsid5445546 Did you get this job through the Ministry of Labour?
